                     ) there is Wickedness in it. It grieves the Spirit of God; It provoked him So, that he sware in his wrath, that he would take Vengeance for it: there is Danger in it. Yet it was a thing Ordinary and common amongst the Fathers of these Hebrews, it was neque Novum, neque Rarum, There is Danger of it.

